        {
          "username": "David Anderson",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "101773787442305061300",
          "user_review_count": 3,
          "user_photo_count": 3,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI3O5PmRLAQtUBoBMbdSKA4UvhwlcAL2ziOzRMqFUHn_MRwsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I rarely go out of my way to write bad reviews but this place did their best to earn it.\n\nTDLR: avoid if you are able.\n\nMinus 1 star for each of the following:\n\n1. Customer service is directly out of a comedy sitcom. The cashier\u2019s office workers specifically are not adequately trained for public-facing operations. My spouse and I had multiple negative interactions with the parking attendants, sustained across multiple days. You would think that a person\u2019s who\u2019s entire job revolves around ensuring the smooth and continuous flow of traffic at a premier hospital in the nation would take that duty seriously, but the attendant could not even be bothered to take out both of his AirPods\n\n2. Very odd fee schedule (e.g., anything more than 1 hour is 28 dollars; 24 hours is 37 dollars).\n\n3. Technical capacity is mediocre. The staff cannot manually operate the turnstiles. After you pay, you have 10 minutes to leave before you encounter these technical difficulties. Partial credit here for being able to process split-cash payments.\n\n4. The garage itself is exceedingly narrow and reckless driving is pervasive. Unnecessarily high risk of collision, especially around the time of shift change.\n\nObligatory one star for:\n\n1. This garage\u2019s only redeeming quality is that it\u2019s not street level parking. Even still, you should just double-park it somewhere else.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT20xaVVVVlVhR0pGUTNWR1IxcHVSRXhaTlRjeFNGRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x7c73f4b8c5e2e808!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm1iUUVUaGJFQ3VGR1puRExZNTcxSFE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 weeks ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-30T21:04:48+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Rohit",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "113352078768784917098",
          "user_review_count": 19,
          "user_photo_count": 2,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLS-3zu6U5eYMKCfo2_Pm3v2F6iNFltsLygxdF3G2SWiBwS_eQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I\u2019m not sure why it\u2019s such a difficult task to self-park at this location. It\u2019s a self-park garage, with substantial space, but the attendants insist on valeting your car. This is highly inconvenient if you\u2019re staying past valet hours and are managing unloading and loading with a child. Further, it adds unnecessary stress and potential health risks, especially when you're already dealing with the emotional and physical toll of having a sick child. The last thing any parent needs is the added burden of coordinating with valet services, particularly if their child requires immediate attention or if they have medical equipment to transport.\n\nMoreover, valeting at a children\u2019s hospital seems counterintuitive. Families are often in vulnerable states, and the priority should be ease and accessibility, not forcing them to navigate additional logistical hurdles. Self-parking allows parents to have direct access to their vehicles at all times, which is crucial in emergencies or when they need to quickly retrieve something for their child.\n\nIt\u2019s also worth considering the health implications. With a sick child, minimizing exposure to unnecessary interactions is key. Valeting involves handing over keys, waiting in lines, and interacting with attendants, which could potentially expose already immunocompromised children to additional risks. In a place dedicated to healing and care, the system should prioritize the well-being and convenience of its visitors.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURRb0pqVzRnRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x7c73f4b8c5e2e808!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgMDQoJjW4gE%7C%7C?hl=en",
